---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout title="Lightmapping in ThreeJS" backHref="/#blog" backLabel="← Back to Blog">
  <div class="prose max-w-none">
    <div class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
      <div class="my-6">
        <img src="/blog/lightmaps/lightmap5.png" alt="Lightmapping in ThreeJS" width="800" height="400" class="w-full" />
      </div>

      <p class="mb-4">
        <a href="https://github.com/lucas-jones/three-lightmap-baker" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bg-black text-white font-bold px-1 py-0.5 hover:bg-gray-800">
          Three Lightmap Baker
        </a> is a project demonstrating GPU-accelerated lightmap generation in Three.js. Built using excellent libraries including Three Mesh BVH, Three GPU Pathtracer, and XAtlas-Three, it showcases how to bake realistic lighting directly in the browser.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-gray-900 mt-8">How it works</h3>

      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4 space-y-4">
        <li class="mb-4">
          Pass all the geometry into <a href="https://github.com/repalash/xatlas-three/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bg-black text-white font-bold px-1 py-0.5 hover:bg-gray-800">XAtlas-Three</a> (UV unwrapping library). This will generate a "UV2" attribute on the geometry.
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4">
          Render the geometries vertices in the UV2 space. Create two textures (resolution being the lightmap resolution), using the gl_FragColor to encode <strong>world position</strong> and the <strong>normal</strong>. This is packing Vec3 data into a texture using the RGB channel.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="my-6 space-y-4">
        <img src="/blog/lightmaps/lightmap6.png" alt="Lightmap UV2 world position texture" width="800" height="400" class="w-full" />
        <img src="/blog/lightmaps/lightmap_combo.png" alt="Lightmap combo texture" width="800" height="400" class="w-full" />
      </div>

      <p class="mb-4 italic">
        <strong>Visual reference:</strong> Using these textures as the lightmap (using UV2).
      </p>

      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4 space-y-4" start="3">
        <li class="mb-4">
          These two textures are effectively a 2D array of World Position &amp; Normals covering the entire geometry.
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4">
          Iterate through each World Position &amp; Normal. Cast rays at each position to calculate incoming light.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="my-6">
        <img src="/blog/lightmaps/lightmap_pixels.png" alt="Lightmap pixels with arrows for world position and normals" width="800" height="400" class="w-full" />
      </div>

      <p class="mb-4 italic">
        <strong>Visual reference:</strong> Creating arrows for each world position &amp; the normal
      </p>

      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4 space-y-4" start="5">
        <li class="mb-4">
          The Three Mesh BVH library helps improve the performance of raycasting, it also allows raycasting on the GPU (this is super fast).
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4">
          Using A LOT of copy &amp; pasted code from Three GPU Pathtracer to generate light
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="my-6 space-y-4">
        <img src="/blog/lightmaps/lightmap7.png" alt="Lightmap result 7" width="800" height="400" class="w-full" />
        <img src="/blog/lightmaps/lightmap8.png" alt="Lightmap result 8" width="800" height="400" class="w-full" />
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-gray-900 mt-8">Further Reading / Watching</h3>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A61S_2swwAc" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bg-black text-white font-bold px-1 py-0.5 hover:bg-gray-800">
            I made a better Ray-Tracing engine
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/GraphicsProgramming/comments/brl22k/high_level_overview_of_a_lightmapping_generation/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bg-black text-white font-bold px-1 py-0.5 hover:bg-gray-800">
            High level overview of a lightmapping generation process
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://ndotl.wordpress.com/2018/08/29/baking-artifact-free-lightmaps/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bg-black text-white font-bold px-1 py-0.5 hover:bg-gray-800">
            Baking artifact-free lightmaps on the GPU
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="http://david-westreicher.github.io/2014/05/31/radiosity/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bg-black text-white font-bold px-1 py-0.5 hover:bg-gray-800">
            Radiosity Baker
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://knarkowicz.wordpress.com/2014/07/20/lightmapping-in-anomaly-2-mobile/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bg-black text-white font-bold px-1 py-0.5 hover:bg-gray-800">
            Lightmapping in Anomaly 2 mobile
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
